Parliament, Monday, 12 March 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Public Enterprises tasked with the inquiry into the mismanagement of state funds in state-owned enterprises have been informed that former South African Airways Chairperson Ms Dudu Myeni and the Gupta brothers and associates will not be attending tomorrow’s meeting. The Gupta have advised the committee that the brothers are currently out of the country and can therefore not accept the request to appear before the inquiry. Regarding Ms Myeni, the committee has been informed that she is unable to attend due to ill health and incapacity. They were all due to testify in front of the inquiry tomorrow. The committee will decide on the way forward regarding the Gupta brothers and Ms Myeni. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE INQUIRY FOR THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC ENTERPRISES, MS ZUKISWA RANTHO For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Yoliswa LanduParliamentary Communication ServicesTel: 021 403 8203Cell: 081 497 4694E-mail: ylandu@parliament.gov.za The President is not a member of Parliament. After an MP is elected as President, he or she loses the seat and the vacancy is filled by the next eligible person from the same party.Read more